# Git Hygiene

- Check `git status` before starting work.
- Use clear branches for agent work: `agent/<role>/<short-task>` or
  `business/<slug>/<short-task>`.
- Commit meaningful units of work with clear messages; include task artifacts and
  verification steps in the PR/commit body.
- Do **not** push directly to `main` unless the mode explicitly allows it
  (`GITHUB_ALLOW_DIRECT_PUSH_TO_MAIN=true`). Prefer a PR-style workflow.
- Never commit secrets (see `01-no-secrets`).

```bash
git checkout -b agent/coder/add-health-endpoint
git add apps/gateway/gateway/main.py
git commit -m "feat(gateway): add /health endpoint with db + redis checks"
```

See [`docs/09-github-workflow.md`](../../docs/09-github-workflow.md) for the full flow.
